Worship Him tonight. “Holy, holy, holy is the LORD Almighty; the whole earth is full of his glory.” Isaiah‬ ‭6:3‬ ‭NIV‬‬
・・・
Custom hand lettering provided by my friend @jefffrandsen. He's an amazingly talented dude. Go check him out.

See giveaway and registration details below.

Thankful that through it all, You are still God and You are still good. (Praise Him tonight) #GoodNewsFeed
Start the day off right. Make this your prayer this morning for whatever comes your way today. #GoodNewsFeed

Just like God knew the plans of those that Nebuchadnezzar had carried into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon, He knows yours. And just like His promise to them, I believe He has "plans to prosper you and not harm you, plans to give hope and a future" even when you feel hopeless or are going through a difficult time. But, we need to be in tune with God and obedient to His word. Pray. Act. Pray. Repeat. #GoodNewsFeed

Take a moment and read that again. "So Christ has set us free." If anyone has been oppressed, they know precisely how amazing freedom is. Christ has set us free from the bondage of sin. THAT'S HUGE! We are no longer salves to sin but set free in Christ. We are now called to a life of righteousness. Let's live boldly in this freedom. // Custom hand lettering contributed by @jefffrandsen.
・・・
“It was for freedom that Christ set us free; therefore keep standing firm and do not be subject again to a yoke of slavery.”
‭‭Galatians‬ ‭5:1 NASB

“And He has said to me, "My grace is sufficient for you, for power is perfected in weakness." Most gladly, therefore, I will rather boast about my weaknesses, so that the power of Christ may dwell in me. Therefore I am well content with weaknesses, with insults, with distresses, with persecutions, with difficulties, for Christ's sake; for when I am weak, then I am strong.”
‭‭2 Corinthians‬ ‭12:9-10‬ ‭NASB‬‬

“What then shall we say to these things? If God is for us, who is against us? He who did not spare His own Son, but delivered Him over for us all, how will He not also with Him freely give us all things? Who will bring a charge against God's elect? God is the one who justifies; who is the one who condemns? Christ Jesus is He who died, yes, rather who was raised, who is at the right hand of God, who also intercedes for us. Who will separate us from the love of Christ? Will tribulation, or distress, or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or peril, or sword?”
‭‭Romans‬ ‭8:31-35‬ ‭NASB‬‬

The God of the Universe, Who holds everything together, has YOU in His hands. What could be more comforting? That's right, nothing. Whatever you are going through, brothers and sisters in Christ, remember this truth. AND hold on to it because He's holding on to you. #GoodNewsFeed
